description: You are given a string s that contains some bracket pairs, with each pair containing a non-empty key. You know the values of a wide range of keys. This is represented by a 2D string array knowledge where each knowledge[i] = [keyi, valuei] indicates that key keyi has a value of valuei. You are tasked to evaluate all of the bracket pairs. When you evaluate a bracket pair that contains some key keyi, you will: Each key will appear at most once in your knowledge. There will not be any nested brackets in s. Return the resulting string after evaluating all of the bracket pairs.
